1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 39-04 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to military sacrifice number plates; and to amend and reenact section
3 39-04-10.3 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to personalized plates.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 39-04-10.3 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 39-04-10.3. Personalized plates.
8 At the request of a registrant, the department may provide special license plates marked
9 with not more than seven numerals, letters, or combinations of numerals and letters, upon
10 application for a special license plate and payment of an additional fee of twenty-five dollars per
11 registration period, unless the plate is a gold star license plate, military sacrifice license plate, or
12 a prisoner of war license plate, then there is no additional charge. A personal plate containing a
13 restricted character may not be renewed. The department shall make the special license plates
14 authorized by this section available for motor vehicles registered under section 39-04-10.6,
15 trailers, travel trailers, and motorcycles. The fee for the special license plates issued under this
16 section for vehicles registered under section 39-04-10.6 is a one-time fee of one hundred
17 dollars. The special license plates for motorcycles may contain not more than six numerals,
18 letters, or a combination of not more than six numerals and letters. In the event of sale or
19 transfer of the vehicle, the owner shall remove the special license plates in accordance with
20 section 39-04-36. Upon payment of the applicable transfer fee, the special license plates may
21 be transferred to a replacement motor vehicle.
22 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 39-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
23 and enacted as follows:
