1 Military sacrifice plates.
2 1. The director shall issue distinctive number plates to individuals eligible under this
3 section upon receiving:
4 a. Payment of all other fees required under this chapter for registration of a motor
5 vehicle; and
6 b. Verification, as determined by the department, of an individual's eligibility status
7 under this section.
8 2. An individual is eligible for a military sacrifice plate if the individual is an immediate
9 family member of a individual who died outside a combat zone while serving honorably
10 and has not been not found guilty of willful misconduct as defined in title 38, Code of
11 Federal Regulations, part 3, subpart a, section 3.1, subsection n, as a current member
12 of any branch of the armed forces of the United States, either active or reserve, the
13 national guard under federal or state control, or the United States coast guard.
14 3. Military sacrifice plates must be inscribed with a distinctive emblem and the words
15 "military sacrifice".
16 4. For purposes of this section "immediate family member" means a:
17 a. Spouse;
18 b. Parent, step-parent, or other individual who acted in loco parentis;
19 c. Sibling, whether of the whole or half-blood, or by adoption;
20 d. Child, including those by adoption, or a step-child; or
21 e. Grandparent.
22 5. The director may issue military sacrifice plates under this section only to the owner of
23 a passenger motor vehicle, a truck the registered gross weight of which does not
24 exceed twenty thousand pounds [9071.85 kilograms], or a motorcycle.
